{"000-section": {"000-title": "Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY-G) Gramin in Bihar to Cover 4.76 Lakh Families by March", "001-normal": "The beneficiary, if himself is a job card holder would also get wage for 90 days at the rate of Rs 177 per day in the Maoist-free districts, and for 95 days at the same rate in the Maoist-hit districts. The beneficiary would also be facilitated a loan of up to Rs. 70000 which he/she can avail as per the requirements.", "002-normal": "**Selection of Beneficiaries**  \n After selection of beneficiaries by the gram Panchayat, the block development officer (BDO) would conduct physical verification of the actual position of house of a beneficiary. Once the physical verification is complete and applicant is found to be eligible, the list would be passed to the district rural development authority office, where it would be put on the designated software.", "003-normal": "Then comes the fund release, the first installment of the financial assistance amount will be transferred into the bank account of the beneficiary."}}